ci Oelze, Starkast, Ste Leema, Stef Schwartz, Stefan Kreimeier, Stefania Ricco, Stefano, Stefano <br>“ Aerel” Veronesi, Stefano Borri, Stefano Oppo, Stefano Stradaioli, Step Christopher, Stephan Bugaj, Stephanie Ann Bailey, Stephanie Cory, Stephanie Heinz, Stephen D. O’Quinn, Stephen J. Schatzman, Stephen Newman, <br>Stephen O’Brien, Stephen Pilch, Stephen Rosania, Stephen Schnoebelen, Steve Wiklund, Steven Barrett, Steven Behringer, Steven Bocchetto, Steven Collins, Steven J. Zeve, Steven M. Smith, StEvil, Stragliotto Domenico, <br>Stratagemma, Stéphane Delleuze, Suemia Biafore, Sugomori, Suguru OIkawa, Susan Haarman, SusanU, Sydney LaBorgia, Sylvia Short, T Loquvam, T&amp;J McCord, Tabi Walters, Tabitha Goicher, Tad Kelson, Takk, Tammy <br>Tran, Tanya Cooley, Tao - Kraken aps, Tara S., Tarna Allen, Tasena, Tats Rabelink, Taylor Sosa, Teal, Tebra Hansing, Technodromo, Teocadista, Terrance Marpoe, Terry McKelvey, Thalie Ré, Thalsturz, Thasaidon, Thasic, <br>THE Donnie, The Grim Reaper, The Mad Catter, The Mesa Family, Thea Flurry, TheBearIsDriving, Theodore Martinez, TheThingFromOuterSpace, TheTokenDiceGuy, thomas delrue, Thomas Di Bennardo, Thomas <br>Freed, Thomas R. Gould III, Thomas Rye, Tiberio “Master Ronin” Azzarà, TIE, Tiffany Espinosa, Tiffany Hamlin, Tiger Richardson, Tim D. Griffin, Tim Doyle, Tim Hall, Tim Kuehlhorn, Tim Smith, Tim Tang, Tina <br>Alexandersen Solvang, TiTi Navalta, To my son Lasse Wauters, Tobias Belek, Todd (Konton) Hangos, Todd Daugherty, Todd Zircher, Tola Séamestré, Tom Burdak, Tom Kraft, Tomasz Chmielik, Tommaso Oddone, <br>Tommy Smekens, Tommy Toresjö, Tony Fucina, Toyka, Trallalaura, Trash Heap Games, Travis “Novoreaper” Boillat, Travis Carrier, Travis Foster, Travis Hartland, Trent Michels, Trever “Kid Vorpal” Harwell, Trevor J.J. <br>Sherman, Trip Space-Parasite, Triston Thorpe, Troy Ellis, Trust-No-One Games, Tseng, Hua-Jui, Tubby McButters, Tucker Williamson, Turtle, Twila Cotter, Ty Logan Rollins, tyler &amp; melissa, Tyler Braden, Tyler Jones, <br>Tyler Reid, Tyler Scholz, Tyler Spaulding, V . Franklin, Valentina Paggiarin, Valerie Lever, Valerio Lucido, Valerio Votadoro, Valian, Vassiliy Clottes, Vaughn McDonald, Vegar Fristad, Veronica Vandersteenen, Vespero, <br>Vicky Efram, Victor G. Balcazar Moctezuma, Victor J Kinzer, Victoria Baker, Victoria Johnsen, Ville Kugelberg, Vincent Goodlove, VnNxNeAhng, Vorgartezwerg, Víctor Romero, w. David Lewis, Wayne Bridge, Wayne <br>Marshall, Welgian Baffle, Weronika Solarek, Wes Cumbee, Wes Woods, whateley0825, WhimsyWanda, Wicked Thing, Will Godar, Will Phillips, Willem B., William Bonacina, William G Schiemenz, William J. Scott III, <br>William Joseph Bechard, William Z. Cohen  MSGT/USMC, ret., WM. Downs, wookwok, Wren, www.despertalia.com, Wynter Storm, Xavier R., Xious Divinshield, Y ann RICCI, Y asmin Estrella, Y ezi Goomer, YLF , <br>Y oshiki KUCHIKURA, Yue, Yuu Gamon, Zach Theis, Zach Y okell, Zachary Alvarado, Zachary Knippel, Zachary Longoria, Zachary Stamper, Zack Holmes, Zack Long, Zak and Beth, Zalyn Harper, Zandermoore, Zane <br>Graves, Zasabi, Zeb Berryman, Zev Rothenberg, ZHULUL-N. AZMAN, Zoltam, ZombieGarou, Zsolt Kertay.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":26800000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241731,"modifiedTime":1783973241731,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"librarySlug":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed-2022-07-01","category":"Core Book","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","sourcePath":"Users\\Gamer\\Documents\\Broken Tales KS [ENG]\\bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf"}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241731,"modifiedTime":1783973241731,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"ZsZapS4lKEue2V2w","name":"bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen","pages":[{"_id":"PML9hY16iYBRL4dF","name":"PDF local","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h1>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen</h1><p><strong>Archivo:</strong> bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf</p><p><strong>Paginas:</strong> 30</p><p><a href=\"#source-pdf-omitted\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Abrir PDF dentro de Foundry</a></p>","markdown":""},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241731,"modifiedTime":1783973241731,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"bPIlgUYxdbR4lOVJ","name":"Pagina 1","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 1</h2><p>Informations on the Sheet.<br> ◆ A brief background is introduced under the Hunter’s <br>name, explaining who the Hunter is and why they joined <br>the Order.<br> ◆ Descriptors indicate what the Hunter does best and <br>what their flaws are. Incorporating a Descriptor into <br>the narration of a Hunter’s actions allows a Position or <br>Defense Check to start from 3 Base Successes. Getting in <br>trouble during the narrative, thanks to the Descriptor’s <br>Downside, allows you to check them off and gain XP .<br> ◆ Gifts are powerful special abilities that only Hunters of the <br>Order possess. They can be used whenever the opportunity <br>arises, following the rules and limitations of the Gift itself.<br> ◆ The Dark Ego  represents their essence and bond to the <br>fairytale world, what the Hunter was before their Breaking <br>Point. Y ou can activate the Dark Ego whenever the <br>Activator’s condition is triggered, or when the Hunter <br>suffers or decides to inflict 1 Wound on themselves. The <br>effect of the Dark Ego persists throughout the course of <br>the Scene.<br> ◆ Equipment indicates what gear the Hunter possesses and <br>can use in order to perform their mission on behalf of the <br>Order.<br> ◆ The Soma value represents the Hunter’s inner strength and <br>ability to tap into the true essence of a Broken Fairytale. <br>Spending Soma increases the chances of a positive <br>Outcome in any Position and Defense Check, or allows <br>the activation of certain Gifts.<br>Player’s Sheet<br>When the Storyteller asks for a <br>Position or Defense Check…<br>Check if one of the Hunter’s Descriptors can help them in the action being <br>performed. If so, the Hunter starts with 3 Base Successes. If no Descriptor <br>is relevant, only 1 Base Success  is obtained. It’s possible to obtain <br>Additional Successes (for example, as a result of a Gift) or Penalties (to <br>be subtracted from the total), to modify the number of Base Successes. Once <br>this is done, the number of  Successes  is compared with the NPC’s or <br>Threat’s Opposition Level declared by the Storyteller. <br>There are 3 Levels of Opposition:<br>Easy 3, Medium 5, Hard 7<br>For an action to have a positive Outcome, you must obtain a total of <br>Successes (given by the sum of Base Successes and Additional Successes) <br>that is at least equal to the Opposition Level you are facing.<br>To get ADDITIONAL <br>SUCCESSES you can...<br> ◆ Spend Soma from the Hunter’s reserve to obtain 1 Additional <br>Success for each point.<br> ◆ Decide to roll one or more 6-sided dice. Y ou gain an Additional <br>Success for each die rolled. However, if even a single die rolls <br>a 1, the entire Check fails. All other results (2-6) count as <br>Additional Successes.<br>How many dice can you roll?<br>Rolling dice is a gamble. Y ou can roll as many dice as you wish to <br>reach the Outcome you desire. However, each additional die rolled <br>increases the chances of rolling a 1, even one of which results in a <br>Failure. Even when aiming for the best Outcome (Outcome with <br>Increment) the total number of Successes needed will never exceed <br>the Opposition Level + 2.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241731,"modifiedTime":1783973241731,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"HfFhLgnJqlBe5bFe","name":"Pagina 2","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 2</h2><p>Find out how it all turns out...<br>If the result is equal to the Opposition Level:  you’ll get <br>an Outcome with a Cost. The Hunter gets what they want but <br>at a Cost chosen by the Storyteller. If it makes sense, the Hunter <br>can also inflict 1 Wound. In a Defense Check the incoming <br>problem is avoided, but with a complication decided by the <br>Storyteller.<br>By scoring 1 point above the Opposition Level:  you’ll <br>get a Standard Outcome. The Hunter gets what they want. <br>In a Defense Check, the problem is handled without any <br>complications. If it makes sense, the Hunter can also inflict 1 <br>Wound.<br>By scoring 2 points above the Opposition Level:  you’ll <br>get an Outcome with an Increment. The Hunter succeeds better <br>than expected and gains an Increment in addition to what they <br>wanted. The Storyteller decides on the additional effect or, <br>alternatively, the special Increment of one of the Hunter’s Gifts <br>can be activated. In the case of a Defense Check, the problem is <br>avoided perfectly and an Increment is also obtained. If it makes <br>sense, the Hunter can also inflict 1 Wound.<br>Once upon a time...<br>If during the Scenario the Hunter gets into trouble and highlights <br>the Downside of one of their Descriptors, the corresponding <br>box must be marked. During an Interlude, each box marked is <br>converted into 1 XP.<br>Declaring an Interlude<br>If Hunters need to catch their breath, a Player can ask <br>the Storyteller for an Interlude between Scene changes. <br>During the Interlude, it is possible to recover 1 Wound <br>or, alternatively, recover 2 Soma. Each Hunter can ask a <br>question of another Hunter to learn more about their past.<br>During an Interlude XP may be spent to obtain <br>additional effects:<br> ◆ Recover 2 Soma for each XP spent.<br> ◆ Recover 1 Wound for each XP spent.<br> ◆ Evolve a Descriptor into a Specialization. For the <br>rest of the Scenario, this will grant 1 Additional <br>Success in each Scene in which it is used for the first <br>time (1 XP).<br> ◆ Obtain a Scenario Gift for the duration of the <br>Scenario (1 XP).<br>Each Interlude, however, represents a use of time. <br>Remember that the Scenario, and the NPCs, may continue <br>to act even when the Hunters aren’t paying attention.A Wound is inflicted...<br>As an effect of a failed Defense Check or as a Cost for an <br>action. Each Wound must be described and annotated in <br>the Bookmark. The Wound narratively affects what the <br>Hunter can do and the Opposition Level of what they <br>face. Whenever you suffer 1 Wound, you can activate your <br>Dark Ego power for the duration of the Scene. A Player <br>may decide to voluntarily inflict a Wound on the Hunter to <br>instantly activate their Dark Ego.<br>When they suffer a third Wound, the Hunter is out of <br>the game or dead. The Storyteller will reveal their fate <br>according to the situation.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241731,"modifiedTime":1783973241731,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"6XyRE3U121QlumAw","name":"Pagina 3","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 3</h2><p>James  <br>the Swordsman</p>","markdown":""},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241731,"modifiedTime":1783973241731,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"dh1mLNUf0bgd8hg0","name":"Pagina 4","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 4</h2><p>Descriptors and Gifts<br>I am a skilled swordsman and possess fine manners, which is why <br>the Order considers me an excellent candidate to move among <br>High Society. I love indulging in good food and dissolute company.<br>• With a Sword or a Smile:  Once per Scene you may <br>perform a gesture of extreme precision with your weapon, such as <br>slipping an object off someone or writing something on a surface. The <br>person observing your skill will either be impressed or intimidated, <br>depending on the Storyteller’s decision. Y ou receive 1 Additional <br>Success when you use the emotion you have aroused to your advantage.<br>I have learned to face monsters and aberrations without being <br>intimidated. The Beast is on my trail because, having tasted my <br>flesh, it can no longer do without it… <br>• Tick-Tock, Here Comes The Beast: While outdoors, you <br>may ask the Storyteller for the Beast to come in search of your flesh.<br>The Beast is a monstrous NPC with the following characteristics: <br>OL Hard 7 – (4 Wounds) <br>Descriptor: I am a great and mighty beast. I overwhelm everything I <br>come across on my way to snatch my prey. <br>Gift – Ravenous Madness: The Beast has an insane craving for your <br>flesh, and will unleash its rage on anyone standing in its way. With its <br>titanic strength, it can tear down trees and walls, and hurl a man away <br>with a single swipe of its huge paws. The Beast is also quite stupid <br>and will leave the Scene as soon as you are out of sight. Y ou receive <br>2 Additional Successes to any Defense Check against it. If the Beast <br>suffers the fourth Wound, it will dissolve. However, it will regenerate <br>and can be used in the next Scene.<br>I have been a lot of things in my life: ship captain, duellist of great <br>renown, and lover of the most beautiful noblewomen. After years of <br>successes and victories, a mysterious child defeated me with deception. <br>This despicable boy led me into the lair of a dangerous beast and, after <br>imprisoning me, left me to be eaten by the monster. I survived, though <br>I lost a hand... I know for certain he who I seek is no human, and I <br>joined the Order to hunt down the child I hate above all else, and thus <br>have my revenge.<br>James<br>the Swordsman<br>I am a man of the world and nothing can really surprise me <br>anymore. I never question myself. After all, I’m the best at <br>what I do.<br>• Dark Ego – I Will have my Satisfaction: When you <br>choose an opponent, there is no escape for them. Once per Scene, you <br>can take an additional action against the target of your challenge (even <br>if you had already acted during this Exchange) to anticipate their move <br>and stop their action with yours. If an opponent inflicts a Wound on <br>you, you savor the taste of the challenge and receive 1 Additional <br>Success at each Check against them for the rest of the Scenario. <br>Activator: You challenge an enemy or otherwise make clear who and <br>how skilled you are.<br>XP<br>Soma<br> 7<br>Equipment <br>A fine dueling blade / A black powder gun / <br>A finely crafted hook / A purple-red cloak / <br>Traveling boots / A precious pair of binoculars <br>/ Valuable rings.<br>Wounds <br>1.<br>2.<br>3.<br>Extra <br>Wound.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241731,"modifiedTime":1783973241731,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"cv6kqbs2wA620gHh","name":"Pagina 5","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 5</h2><p>Garou  <br>the Old Wolf</p>","markdown":""},"sort":500000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241731,"modifiedTime":1783973241731,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"loiwzONZdCgVdj78","name":"Pagina 6","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 6</h2><p>Garou  <br>the Old Wolf<br>Descriptors and Gifts<br>My senses are unfailing. Nothing can escape my sense of <br>smell and that is why the Order uses me as a guardian. I <br>hate strong smells and loud noises because they feel like <br>burning irons to acute senses.<br>• Find Them Forever After: Once you catch someone’s <br>scent, you never forget it. During a Scene, you can spend 1 Soma to <br>memorize the scent of a person you are interacting with. Y ou will <br>always recognize it and it will be easy for you to follow its traces <br>even after some time. If you concentrate, you can hear a noise even <br>at great distances. When someone approaches you, the Storyteller <br>will warn you long before anyone else in the Scene would notice.<br>A true predator knows how to appear as the most helpless <br>of lambs. I know how to disguise myself. My confidence is <br>boundless and I often tend to underestimate danger, ready <br>to risk anything for a tasty bite.<br>• Wolf Among the Lambs: Y ou may spend 1 Soma to <br>assume the shape of a common human. Create a Descriptor that <br>represents you and includes at least one of these words: Old, <br>Helpless, Weak. In your human form you can speak and act <br>without problems, but, as soon as you use your Dark Ego, you will <br>immediately lose the effect of Wolf Among the Lambs. Y ou receive <br>1 Additional Success when you use the Descriptor you created to <br>deceive someone and catch them off guard.<br>I am a mountain wolf and far more cunning than the stupid villagers who <br>tremble at the mere sight of me. I have lived proudly at the head of my pack, <br>leading a thousand raids and eating succulent, tender morsels of human flesh. <br>But I am not so old I cannot face those who hate me the most, though I may be <br>hunted and reviled. Now that I’m part of the Order, I use my strength to defend <br>the weak hunters who are my companions, knowing that with a single bite I <br>could end their insignificant lives.<br>I am fiercer and more powerful than any human and my fangs <br>can pierce even metal. My proud wolf spirit is everything to me.<br>• Dark Ego - The Big Bad Wolf: Y ou are hardened by a lifetime <br>in the great mountains and your skill is matched only by your courage. <br>When you unleash your rage, create a Descriptor for it that includes <br>at least one of these words: Strong, Fierce, Unstoppable. Y ou can <br>employ the strength of three men, gnaw through stone as easily as flesh, <br>or break down any barrier. When you act using this special Descriptor <br>for Position Checks, you get 1 Additional Success. Once per Scene, you <br>can unleash your rage and receive 3 Additional Successes instead of 1.<br>Activator: You assume the form of a Wolf or reveal yourself for what you <br>really are, scaring off weak humans.<br>Equipment <br>A necklace of stones and wood that I carry in a paw, <br>a token of the only human I do not consider food / <br>Knick-knacks, keys and other junk that I sometimes <br>vomit up from my large stomach.<br>Wounds <br>1.<br>2.<br>3.<br>Extra <br>Wound.<br>XP<br>Soma<br> 6</p>","markdown":""},"sort":600000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241731,"modifiedTime":1783973241731,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"0gmRxTUQZnq0Ok1q","name":"Pagina 7","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 7</h2><p>The Astonishing<br>Pied Piper     Without a Name</p>","markdown":""},"sort":700000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241731,"modifiedTime":1783973241731,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"oaflGEqCLfnPpQGN","name":"Pagina 8","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 8</h2><p>Descriptors and Gifts<br>With my pipe I can play any melody and touch the hearts of <br>living beings. Art needs time to express itself.<br>• Soul Music: When you play your pipes you can spend 1 <br>Soma to sing a special melody. Choose from:<br>1. Imparting an emotion:  Create a Descriptor that represents <br>the emotional state you wish to convey. Everybody present will <br>receive that Descriptor for the current Scene. Y ou may have to <br>make a Position Check to affect opponents.<br>2. Bewitching animals: Y ou may give simple commands to <br>animals that hear your melody. If they show an aggressive attitude, <br>you have to make a successful Position Check for your melody to <br>take effect. As long as you are playing, you may ask the animals to <br>do simple actions such as moving or following a simple command.<br>I am a skilled acrobat and musician. My talent is unrivaled <br>and the Order has chosen me for my ability to capture people’s <br>attention and stimulate their emotions. When I am in the grip <br>of artistic inspiration, I am totally divorced from reality.<br>• Skilled Acrobat: When you sing, dance, or move with <br>grace, you always put on a great show. As an additional action, you <br>can spend 1 Soma and decide on one of the following effects:<br>1. Y ou can make an incredible leap, many feet high, without <br>anyone being able to stop you.<br>2. Y ou may take an object, even if it is worn by an enemy.<br>3. Y ou can perform a minor action with a stunt, such as opening <br>a door or flipping a switch, and then return exactly to where you <br>started.<br>As an artist I have traveled to many places and I know many <br>myths and legends. I’m hungry for knowledge and I’m fascinated <br>by everything I don’t know.<br>• Dark Ego - The Power of Music:  Once per Scene, you <br>can make a sound that can be heard by whomever you wish,<br>even from a great distance. Everyone who hears it suffers 1 Wound, <br>fragile objects break, and frightened animals flee. Alternatively, you <br>can play a gentle melody and the wind itself will obey you, carrying <br>your message to whomever you wish, wherever they are. When using <br>The Power of Music, you can also activate a Soul Music effect on one <br>or more targets of your choice.<br>Activator: Demonstrate your art to its fullest extent, with a show that <br>cannot be ignored.<br>XP<br>Soma<br> 5<br>Equipment <br>A precious pipe of the finest workmanship <br>/ A theater mask / A cloak of many colors / <br>Multicolored chalks and powders / An old ocarina, <br>the first instrument I ever played / Hamelin, my <br>faithful trained mouse.<br>Wounds <br>1.<br>2.<br>3.<br>Extra <br>Wound.<br>  <br>The Astonishing<br>Pied Piper       Without a Name<br>I have always made my art my reason for living. I can play so skillfully that it might as well be magic. I <br>have learned to use the power of music to reach into the souls of both humans and animals. Unfortunately, <br>I have lost count of the number of times I have performed dishonorable acts while pursuing the perfect <br>melody. Having been guilty of various crimes and having taken revenge on those who mocked my sincere <br>love for music, I serenely waited for my execution. The Order freed me in exchange for a promise to <br>serve them and put my skills to work in the fight against Darkness. It was in the darkest moments that I <br>glimpsed the perfect melody, so perhaps as a Hunter, I can find it and make it my own.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":800000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241731,"modifiedTime":1783973241731,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"sH7QbaiuFvjkZnW0","name":"Pagina 9","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 9</h2><p>Babayaga<br>The Child Witch</p>","markdown":""},"sort":900000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241731,"modifiedTime":1783973241731,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"yihSyqrAGgJgSLud","name":"Pagina 10","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 10</h2><p>I  am a child witch, and my power is equal only to my ambition. I did not have a childhood, for I was born <br>already aware of my abilities. To most, I seem cynical and cruel. That is because they do not understand <br>that they are pawns, insignificant pieces in the bloody games that witches and warlocks play. The Order <br>does not look down on my age, which is why it has given me the leadership I deserve.<br>Like any respectable sorceress, I carry my trusty bag full of herbs, <br>poisons, and all kinds of magic tools. My childlike appearance is often <br>useful, but sometimes it leads others to underestimate me. I hate that.<br>• Dark Ego - The Evil Witch: Receive 1 Additional Success on any <br>Check when you use one of your spells, either through the Magic Gift or by <br>inserting it into your narrative through the Descriptors. Moreover, you can <br>unleash your evil aura to gain one or more of the following effects:<br>1. Animals and ordinary people are tormented by your presence and will <br>flee in terror. <br>2. Y ou gain 1 Additional Success if you use your magic to punish someone <br>for breaking a promise or agreement you made earlier.<br>3. In the area around you, you can summon daylight or darkness.<br>Activator: Scare ordinary people or dispense punishment through your <br>magic.<br>XP<br>Soma<br> 5<br>Equipment <br>An old and worn-out black cloak/ A bag of magical <br>ingredients / A small, curved dagger / A rag doll / The <br>Ring of the Order / A lucky elderberry branch / The <br>keys of a strange hut in a tree, which is always in my <br>vicinity.<br>Wounds <br>1.<br>2.<br>3.<br>Extra <br>Wound.<br>Baba yaga<br>       The Child Witch<br>Descriptors and Gifts<br>I am a sorceress and my magical powers allow me to do <br>whatever I want. I need the right amount of time to cast my <br>spells.<br>• Magic: When you want to achieve something, you may <br>use witchcraft. Choose what you want with a sentence like: I want <br>to fly on that old broom, or I want to look like a demon in the <br>eyes of those fools. Y our spell must be focused on an object in <br>your possession, such as a broom to fly or a mask you can wear <br>to look like a demon. Pay a cost from 0 to 2 Soma, decided by <br>the Storyteller, to activate your spell for the duration of a Scene. <br>Remember that you can’t ask for someone’s sudden death, but you <br>can inflict Wounds with your actions through magic.<br>I am very skilled at reading people, that is why the Order has <br>chosen me as leader of the Hunters. I love manipulating people <br>and I often do it merely to amuse myself.<br>• Listen to my Words: Once per Scene, when you talk to <br>someone, you can ask the Storyteller a question about them. The <br>question must be regarding their behaviour, such as any vices or <br>their desires they might have. Y ou gain 1 Additional Success in any <br>action where you exploit what you’ve discovered.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":1000000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241731,"modifiedTime":1783973241731,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"20IwaSCha1Qx8kMR","name":"Pagina 11","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 11</h2><p>Regina<br>The Thief Of Hearts</p>","markdown":""},"sort":1100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241731,"modifiedTime":1783973241731,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"LY3FDobvkx7wdt6x","name":"Pagina 12","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 12</h2><p>I was born to be a leader and I have always surrounded myself with faithful followers ready <br>to satisfy my every whim. Lacking the benefit of noble birth, the power I held was pried from the <br>hands of those less deserving to wield it, no matter the cost. I ruled armies of thugs, and broke <br>the hearts of both men and women. After each conquest, I set out in search of a bigger challenge. <br>Because there is still so much out there that should be rightfully mine, I always want more. The <br>Order has given me a new purpose, a new perspective, and new creatures to enslave.<br>I have an enviable charm and love to dress up to fit the role I have <br>chosen. Even when I try to restrain myself, I never go unnoticed.<br>• Dark Ego - As I Want!:  Y ou know that your way is the only <br>right way to do things. During the Scene, as an additional action, you can <br>choose another character who will be issued a <br>command. In the case of <br>an ally, if they do exactly what you tell them, they will receive 1 Additional <br>Success to their action or increase their Opposition Level by 1. If you give <br>a peremptory order to ensnare an enemy, they will lower their Opposition <br>Level by 1 or, if you’ve already seen it in action, you can prevent them <br>from using one of their Gifts. Once per Scene, you can shout, drawing <br>everyone’s attention to you. For a few moments, they will pause to listen <br>to what you have to say.<br>Activator: Take control of a situation and impose your decisions by <br>dramatically drawing attention to yourself.<br>XP<br>Soma<br> 6<br>Equipment <br>A long leather whip with metal studs and spikes / <br>A beautiful fan behind which to hide your face / <br>Dresses for every occasion / A long burgundy cape / <br>Gold and jewels, gifts from my countless suitors / A <br>sharp stiletto that I use as a hairpin.<br>Wounds <br>1.<br>2.<br>3.<br>Extra <br>Wound.<br>Regina<br>   The Thief Of Hearts<br>Descriptors and Gifts<br>I am determined to get what I want, and nothing will get in <br>my way. I will kill, humiliate, or conquer anything that stands <br>between me and my objective. As you can imagine, I sincerely <br>hate being told no!<br>• I Want It!: When you act with clear and direct intention to <br>achieve an objective, you get 1 Additional Success on each Position <br>Check. Once per Session, you can turn a Failure into an Outcome <br>with Increment. Describe how you grit your teeth and fight to get <br>what you want.<br>Thanks to my contacts and charisma, I always have an ace <br>up my sleeve: followers ready to help me and allies who owe <br>me favors. Maintaining an empire of beneficial connections <br>requires commitment and resources.<br>• The Queen: During a Scene you always have a couple of <br>trusted servants with you, ready to execute your every order. <br>Create a Descriptor for each, which represents the skill for which <br>you hold them in your service. Y our servants will do their best to <br>satisfy your every wish. Decide how you pay them. The Storyteller, <br>when and if they deem it necessary, will ask you to honor their <br>services so as not to lose the use of this Gift for the rest of the <br>Scene. Y ou can check this Descriptor multiple times to get XP .</p>","markdown":""},"sort":1200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241731,"modifiedTime":1783973241731,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"MUm1IEtnH1YiT7Ww","name":"Pagina 13","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 13</h2><p>Babai the Judge</p>","markdown":""},"sort":1300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241731,"modifiedTime":1783973241731,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"5STuCDLjI9Lbfuxr","name":"Pagina 14","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 14</h2><p>XP<br>Soma<br> 6<br>Equipment <br>A precious elegant black dress / A cape and a top hat <br>/ A sturdy cane with a hidden blade / A monocle lens <br>/ An exquisitely crafted Larva (typical mask of the <br>Venice Carnival) / An accurate pocket watch.<br>Wounds <br>1.<br>2.<br>3.<br>Extra <br>Wound.<br>After years of honorable service as State Inquisitor of the Republic of Venice, my body and <br>spirit have undergone a rare mutation and fear is now unknown to me. People have always <br>called me Bogeyman, fearing the justice that I represented. Perhaps my own absence of <br>fear made me even more terrifying in the eyes of mortals. The Order has given me a new <br>assignment because even in the fight against darkness, someone needs to be ready to judge <br>what is right and what is wrong.<br>My presence intimidates people, touching the fear that dwells deep in <br>their hearts. The presence of children and their innocent way of looking <br>at the world makes me uneasy.<br>• Dark Ego - If you don’t Stop, I’ll Call the Bogeyman!: <br>Y ou are like a sinuous shadow that can reach anywhere. During a Scene, <br>you can arrive at a location by covering any distance and overcoming <br>any obstacle if one of your allies or an NPC calls your name. When you <br>manifest your true nature, everyone who witnesses it will be frightened <br>and will not act against you unless you threaten them first. The Storyteller <br>may ask you for a Position Check to frighten particularly powerful <br>characters. Receive 1 Additional Success on all Defense Checks you make <br>against the actions of someone who is now fearful.<br>Activator: Enter or leave a shadow by manifesting your true nature and <br>scaring someone.<br>Descriptors and Gifts<br>I am good at understanding, evaluating, and grasping every <br>hidden detail, which is why the Order wanted me as a judge. <br>I am cold, methodical, and cannot stand when plans change <br>abruptly.<br>• Eye of the Judge:  Once per Scene, when you meet a <br>group of NPCs you will immediately understand who is the most <br>and the least capable of them. Moreover, the Storyteller will also <br>reveal to you if there are relationships such as love, hate, or fidelity <br>between two NPCs of your choice. Receive 1 Additional Success <br>when you use the information you have discovered to intimidate <br>or question someone.<br>My body is made of pure shadow and I can become intangible <br>for brief moments. I hate sunlight and cannot properly focus <br>when not surrounded by a comforting shadow.<br>• Like a Shadow: Y ou can spend 1 Soma to manipulate the <br>shadows to your advantage, choose from:<br>1. Acquire a small object, even if it is held by someone, as long as <br>you can see it. <br>2. Make an object in your immediate vicinity topple down. <br>3. Stretch a shadow and manipulate its shape to make it look <br>different.<br>Additionally, you always receive 1 Additional Success on any <br>Defense Check you make while in a shaded area. If you get a <br>successful Outcome, as an additional effect you can move from <br>one shadow to another and no one can prevent it.<br>Babai<br>the Judge</p>","markdown":""},"sort":1400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241731,"modifiedTime":1783973241731,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"UEXjtpuJshKxvGPS","name":"Pagina 15","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 15</h2><p>The Woman<br>    from the Wood</p>","markdown":""},"sort":1500000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241731,"modifiedTime":1783973241731,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"5VXO9UIxvs16al1N","name":"Pagina 16","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 16</h2><p>Descriptors and Gifts<br>I am incredibly strong. Despite my petite looks, I am tougher than <br>the sturdiest of men. I struggle to control my strength and often <br>end up damaging things unintentionally.<br>• The Woman from the Wood:  Y ou receive 1 Additional <br>Success to any Position Check that requires you to resort to your <br>strength. If you eliminate a living being by causing a Wound, you can <br>do it in an extremely disturbing way. Anyone who witnesses it, at the <br>discretion of the Storyteller, will lower their Opposition Level by 1 for <br>the next action.<br>Sometimes I manifest strange abilities, the legacy of a past that I <br>no longer remember. But, when I need it, the world around me <br>shapes itself to protect and shelter me. I hate being out in the open <br>and being the center of attention.<br>• Home Sweet Home: Y ou can spend 1 Soma to draw on the <br>strange powers of the witch you once were. When you do so, choose <br>one of the following effects.<br>1. Create a shelter for one person, perfectly camouflaged within the <br>environment. It is very difficult to discover your shelter, though some <br>NPCs can come close. At the Storyteller’s discretion, a Defense Check <br>may be made to see if you’re discovered.<br>2. Reshape a plant. Y ou can, for instance, create a ladder with the <br>branches of a tree or weave branches to act as a shield.<br>3. Make something disgusting/rotten edible, giving it a sweet and <br>enticing appearance. Anyone other than you who consumes your <br>sweet recovers 1 Wound.<br>My memory is gone. The first thing I remember is the Order finding me, wandering in <br>the woods naked and covered in blood. I possess extraordinary strength and a feral instinct, <br>such that any civilized society ought to chain me like a monster. I know that in my past is a sin <br>so great, my memory could not bear the weight of it. But, I want to remember and perhaps <br>by serving the Order I will be able to do so. I have a natural soft spot for children, and I can’t <br>stand to see them get hurt. The Order uses me as a weapon in the most serious matters when <br>it is necessary to act decisively and demonstrate that a Hunter is a force to be reckoned with.<br>The Woman<br>from the Wood<br>I love human flesh and can gain insight about people just <br>looking at them. I am helplessly attracted to those who have a <br>particular physical trait that stimulates my appetite, such as a <br>good smell or velvety skin.<br>• Dark Ego - Soft and Succulent Flesh: The truth is that you crave human flesh , especially when raw and taken from evil <br>people. When you inflict a Wound through violent action on someone <br>you deem evil, and if you reach an Outcome with an Increment, you <br>may inflict 1 additional Wound. Once per Scene when you consume <br>human flesh , you recover 1 Wound and the Storyteller will reveal <br>some memories of the victim, giving you contextualized information <br>about what you are looking for. <br>Activator: Blatantly manifest your desire to devour human flesh , regardless of the consequences.<br>XP<br>Soma<br> 6<br>Equipment <br>A doll and a little wooden soldier, the only items I had <br>with me when I was found. I don’t know where they come <br>from, but I treasure them / A worn out, gray travel dress, <br>on which one can see bloodstains / A sharp butcher’s <br>knife / A hair ribbon, a gift from a Hunter of the Order / <br>A cookbook with recipes for cakes and sweets.<br>Wounds <br>1.<br>2.<br>3.<br>Extra <br>Wound.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":1600000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241732,"modifiedTime":1783973241732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Kf5zTQB5WMvVrOab","name":"Pagina 17","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 17</h2><p>TheImmortal</p>","markdown":""},"sort":1700000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241732,"modifiedTime":1783973241732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"PQghY2Y4PdCSUhmS","name":"Pagina 18","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 18</h2><p>TheImmortal<br>Descriptors and Gifts<br>I have knowledge and wisdom drawn from centuries of <br>existence, which I can conjure to mind when needed. <br>I often get lost in the memories of my past glories, <br>forgetting about the world around me.<br>• Memories of an Infinite Life: Y ou have been <br>alive for an indefinite time and know almost everything. <br>Once per Scene, you may ask for information about the <br>past or a specific subject or place, which is only available <br>to you due to your long history. The Storyteller will provide <br>relevant and useful details that may be available to you due <br>to your experiences. Once per Scene, you may change the <br>above Descriptor associated with this Gift (but not the <br>Drawback) to one that represents a skill you have conjured <br>to your immortal mind. This new Descriptor is yours until <br>the end of the Scene and you receive 1 Additional Success <br>the first time you use it for a Check.<br>The Order uses my powers for their own purposes and <br>I have had to become skilled at understanding and <br>supporting the needs of my allies as a result. Although <br>I hate to admit it, over time I have begun to take some <br>pleasure in doing good deeds.<br>• The Servant: Once per Scene, as an additional <br>action, you can grant 1 Additional Success to an ally’s action <br>if you can narratively support them. Y ou can also always <br>spend your Soma to pay the activation cost of your allies’ <br>Gifts.<br>I m a sorcerer who has found the key to immortality. Long life has only whetted my appetite for power <br>and in its pursuit, I have been stained by every sin.  The secret behind my unending existence is that I <br>have hidden my soul, removing it from my body. Unfortunately, the Order found its hiding place and now <br>it is held beyond my reach in a fortified church, leaving me no choice but to submit to their commands. <br>Guilty of one thousand and one crimes, the Order demands I balance each with one thousand and one acts <br>of virtue. According to those foolish preachers, they are leading me down the path of redemption. In truth, <br>the Order treats me as a servant, giving to me only the most thankless tasks, knowing that I can not be <br>subdued by death. I remain humble and silent, waiting for the day when I will discover where they have <br>hidden my soul. Then I will unleash my revenge and annihilate the entire Papacy...<br>My body is but a tool which I can manipulate at will, far beyond common <br>human limits. In spite of my old and emaciated appearance, I feel neither fatigue <br>nor pain. With matters of the flesh no longer of concern, I value beautiful things <br>and works of art above anything else.<br>• Dark Ego - The Immortal:  When you suffer 1 Wound, you can <br>immediately spend 1 Soma to remain conscious, allowing you to suffer many <br>Wounds without dying. Y ou are in full control of your body, even parts that have <br>been cut off. Y ou can see through a torn eye or continue to use your severed hand, <br>so don’t skimp on describing a Wound when you suffer it. At the end of the Scene <br>in which you activated your Dark Ego, you recover all the Wounds suffered except <br>the first one. Y our body regenerates and the severed parts are reattached in a horrid <br>spectacle that few have the stomach to watch.<br>Activator: Use your indifference to pain or death to your advantage, revealing your <br>true nature for anyone to see.<br>Equipment <br>Poor clothes / A worn out sickle, a reminder of times past / A <br>small bag with some precious items that you have collected <br>in your adventures / A key that opens the door of one of your <br>many secret refuges / A papal ring, symbol of your indenture <br>to the Church / A little toy, given to you by whoever you <br>helped with your first good deed.<br>Wounds <br>1.<br>2.<br>3.<br>Extra <br>Wound.<br>XP<br>Soma<br> 7</p>","markdown":""},"sort":1800000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241732,"modifiedTime":1783973241732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"3mCfkFXzPwKCz5be","name":"Pagina 19","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 19</h2><p>Marina <br>the Sea <br>Explorer</p>","markdown":""},"sort":1900000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241732,"modifiedTime":1783973241732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"6UGWlBj7BlUNZ9nQ","name":"Pagina 20","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 20</h2><p>I am a traveler, and, over the years, I have visited every location known to man. Being a <br>traveling merchant has allowed me to easily hide my talents as a witch from prying eyes. Year <br>after year, I have accumulated all kinds of magical and mundane wealth. But the Order found <br>me and forced me to sign the most one-sided contract of my entire career as a trader. Now <br>I must put my skills and my charisma at the service of the Order, trying to earn as much as <br>possible to redeem the enormous debt that they have made me incur through deceit.<br>I have a massive collection of magical relics and treasures. I am very <br>stingy with my collection and constantly seeking to add to my wealth <br>so I can redeem my freedom.<br>• Dark Ego - Treasures of the Sea:  At the beginning of <br>the Scenario, you receive 2 Treasure Tokens. When you show off your <br>Treasures, spend 1 Treasure Token and 1 Soma, and create a Descriptor <br>that represents it such as Wolf-Slaying Dagger or Lens of Truth. Receive 1 <br>Additional Success for any Check in which your Treasure may be helpful. <br>Alternatively, spend 1 Token to draw a Potion from your pouch to give <br>to someone. Create a Descriptor to represent its magical effect such as <br>Seeing in the dark or Extraordinary strength. Whoever drinks it will be <br>granted the Descriptor you created for 1 Scene, plus 1 Additional Success <br>on the first action in which they use the advantage given by the potion. <br>When you obtain a new treasure or close a favorable deal, you receive 1 <br>Treasure Token.<br>Activator: Turn a request for help or a conversation into a negotiation, <br>making it clear how amazing your treasures are.<br>XP<br>Soma<br> 6<br>Equipment <br>Exotic and colorful dresses / A large bag full of treasures / A <br>travel bag / Rings and fine jewelry made out of seashells / <br>A vial of sea water / Cosmetics and perfumes.<br>Wounds <br>1.<br>2.<br>3.<br>Extra <br>Wound.<br>Marina <br>the Sea <br>Explorer<br>Descriptors and Gifts<br>I am a sea witch, and as such, I have the power to shape water <br>and move it at will. I hate enclosed places, cut off from the <br>presence of my beloved sea.<br>• Sea Magic:  Y ou can unleash your witch powers and <br>control seawater, manipulating it as if it were solid. Y ou can use <br>it as a weapon or as an object to support your actions, giving it the <br>consistency of a whip that can reach up to thirty feet. When you <br>act, you can take a second supporting action, such as picking up <br>something, moving someone you want to defend, or hindering an <br>enemy’s movement thanks to the water you manipulate. Y ou can <br>also use this Gift with fresh water, but you will need to spend 1 <br>Soma to do so.<br>Nobody knows my true form, which I hide under an appearance <br>of eternal youth. I can change shape to some extent, while still <br>remaining in human form. I am hopelessly attracted to all <br>forms of beauty and I often get lost in contemplating it.<br>• Mutable Appearance: Once per Scene you can change <br>your appearance. Create a Descriptor that represents your new <br>appearance. Nobody can pierce your deception, except through <br>magical means or Gifts that allow one to discover the truth. In <br>addition, you may spend 1 Soma to take the specific appearance of <br>a person you have already met, mimicking their voice and manners <br>as well. Y ou can keep your new appearance until the Scene is over.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":2000000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241732,"modifiedTime":1783973241732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"mlNGfYhpn6kxkwpY","name":"Pagina 21","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 21</h2><p>Niklaus<br>   von Krampus</p>","markdown":""},"sort":2100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241732,"modifiedTime":1783973241732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"xLBbZOdd9wTmFAaD","name":"Pagina 22","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 22</h2><p>Niklaus<br>von Krampus<br>Descriptors and Gifts<br>I am a skilled exorcist. I know how to identify and fight <br>evil through prayer and the sacred arts. Despite what I <br>am, I hate holy places and manifestations of faith and <br>religion, as they cause the demon inside me to stir.<br>• Exorcist: When you face a clearly supernatural being, <br>you gain 1 Additional Success on all Checks. Y ou can also <br>invoke sacred rites and prayers to disturb the evil you face. If a <br>subject, artifact, or supernatural manifestation uses a Gift that <br>you know of or have already seen in action, you can spend 1 <br>Soma to prevent its use. Each time you activate this Gift, roll 1 <br>die. If you roll a 5 or a 6, you gain 1 Devil Token.<br>I am good at understanding people and helping them. <br>Now, thanks to the demon that dwells in me, I can even <br>perceive the dark side of people. Every so often, however, <br>the demon takes over, making me behave strangely in <br>front of ordinary people.<br>• The Inner Demon: Once per Scene, you can release <br>the inner demon, whether that’ d be yours or someone else’s. In <br>your case, create a Descriptor that represents an emotion that <br>includes the word Anger, Envy, or Wickedness. Y ou receive 2 <br>Additional Successes the first time you use this Descriptor for <br>a Position Check. If you unleash someone else’s inner demon, <br>the Storyteller will create a Descriptor for them that showcases <br>their hidden, dark side. When using this Gift on particularly <br>powerful individuals, the Storyteller may request a Position <br>Check from you to succeed. Each time you use this Gift, you <br>receive 1 Devil Token.<br>I am a devoted clergyman who has always dedicated his life to helping others. Over the years I have <br>become a talented exorcist and this vocation of mine led me to the remote village of Borgo Maleanime. <br>There, I fought a particularly insidious demon, who concealed itself among the ranks of a gang of young <br>thugs who merely pretended to be demons to scare people. It was a tough fight, but I finally got the better <br>of the fiend. Or so I thought. Something in the exorcism did not go as expected and now the demon dwells <br>inside me, sowing fear and pain whenever it re-emerges. The Order welcomed me into its ranks as an <br>exorcist and I gladly accepted this role, with the hope that the missions entrusted to me would allow me to <br>find a way to rid myself, once and for all, of that which hides within me.<br>The demon in me grants me its power, allowing me to act with savage strength <br>and speed. It is not easy to contain this ferocity and, often, I end up hurting or <br>destroying things I did not wish to.<br>• Dark Ego - The Demon Revealed: While generally retaining control, <br>every now and then you have to allow the demon to manifest and unleash its <br>anger. Create a Descriptor that represents your demonic form and that includes <br>at least one of these words: Monstrous , Fierce, Beastly. Y our physical abilities go <br>far beyond those of a mere mortal, but you will behave like a devil, enjoying the <br>evil and fear you inspire. When you act using this special Descriptor, you gain 1 <br>Additional Success. Y ou can spend 1 Devil Token to inflict 1 additional Wound or <br>to spend as Soma for a Check. Once per Scenario, the Storyteller can spend 1 Devil <br>Token to activate this Gift against your will.<br>Activator: Give free rein to your demonic side or listen to the sound of bells or cowbells <br>for at least one minute.<br>Equipment <br>An old cassock, worn out by many travels / Exorcism vestments <br>and tools / An old pouch where you find things that the demon <br>takes when it is in control (often, things with unclear origins <br>you don’t wish to know about) / A shepherd’s curved staff of <br>wood and iron to beat the devil with / Precious and small relics <br>received as offerings / An old and time-worn bible.<br>XP<br>Soma<br> 6<br>Wounds <br>1.<br>2.<br>3.<br>Extra <br>Wound.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":2200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241732,"modifiedTime":1783973241732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"YCzLq5hWO6jf9YgH","name":"Pagina 23","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 23</h2><p>George<br>The Holy<br>Dragon <br>Slayer</p>","markdown":""},"sort":2300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241732,"modifiedTime":1783973241732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"V4FZmLz9LupliCro","name":"Pagina 24","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 24</h2><p>Descriptors and Gifts<br>I have dedicated my life to slaying monsters and <br>aberrations, honing my body and my skill for that <br>purpose. My strict discipline makes me rarely inclined to <br>forgive the mistakes of others.<br>• The Dragon Slayer:  Y ou’re skilled at slaying <br>monsters and demonic creatures in the name of faith. Y ou <br>start each Scenario with 1 Fervor Token. When facing an <br>enemy that is obviously monstrous, if you get a successful <br>Outcome on a Position Check, you can spend 1 Fervor Token <br>to inflict 1 additional Wound. When such an enemy attempts <br>to overwhelm you using one of their Gifts, you can spend <br>1 Fervor Token to receive 2 Additional Successes to your <br>Defense Check. When you suffer 1 Wound, you receive 1 <br>Fervor Token.<br>I have vowed to eradicate all evil from this world and <br>nothing can escape my inquisitive gaze. I hate all secrets, <br>for I know that the seed of evil may grow within anyone.<br>• Agent of the Papacy: When you speak to a crowd  <br>you can infuse their hearts with the light of faith. Spend 1 <br>Fervor Token and you can create a Descriptor that represents <br>a feeling of faith, anger, and a desire for justice against evil. <br>Alternatively, create a Descriptor that represents trust and <br>submission in such faith. The crowd will act accordingly for <br>the rest of the Scene, but particularly powerful NPCs may be <br>immune to your words. Receive 1 Additional Success on any <br>Check you make using the sentiment you inspired. When you <br>publicly expose evil, you receive 1 Fervor Token.<br>I am the most skilled and trusted agent of the Papacy and as such, it is my responsibility <br>to make sure that the fight against darkness never falters. As a child, I fell into a river and <br>almost drowned, but was saved by a creature that I later discovered was a dragon. When I <br>grew up, I took holy vows and joined the Church. In doing so, I discovered that what I believed <br>to be my savior was actually a creature of darkness, ready to steal my soul. I vowed to fight <br>the darkness, suppressing the feeling of gratitude toward the dragon that saved me, which has <br>always plagued me. Such weakness represents a crack through which evil could slither in. No <br>mercy for monsters, no forgiveness for those who would join and serve the forces of evil.<br>George The Holy<br>Dragon Slayer<br>I am a saint in the eyes of ordinary people and no door remains closed <br>for me. My word is that of the Church itself. What I say is not to be <br>questioned.<br>• Dark Ego - The Saint:  When you channel sacred divine power, <br>everyone bows their heads. Ordinary people will show you reverence, while <br>weaker enemy NPCs (at the Storyteller’s discretion) won’t target you unless <br>you’re the only available option, nor will they try to get in your way. In <br>your presence, anyone possessing powers linked to the supernatural lowers <br>their Opposition Level by 1. Y our holy aura emits an intense light that can <br>illuminate the whole area around you at your will.  <br>Activator: Invoke holy divine power by reproaching all sinners and providing <br>an example of purity and righteousness.<br>XP<br>Soma<br> 6<br>Equipment <br>My sacred armor / A sword and a spear blessed by the Pope <br>himself / My proud war stallion / A cross with the Keys of Saint <br>Peter engraved, as a universal symbol of power / <br>Aldebrand, <br>my trusty squire and servant / Papal papers and seals / A cloak <br>of fine workmanship.<br>Wounds <br>1.<br>2.<br>3.<br>Extra <br>Wound.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":2400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241732,"modifiedTime":1783973241732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"nDUjQzKwkclXdZq1","name":"Pagina 25","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 25</h2><p>Sun<br>Wukong<br>the Amazing <br>Monkey</p>","markdown":""},"sort":2500000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241732,"modifiedTime":1783973241732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"5l7Qa3D1DtL9Az4h","name":"Pagina 26","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 26</h2><p>Sun Wukong<br>the Amazing Monkey<br>Descriptors and Gifts<br>I am a skilled guardian. My body is strong and hardened, <br>my senses sharp and alert. Years of captivity have made me <br>submissive, and I struggle not to follow every order I am <br>given.<br>• Guardian Disciple: Y ou can intercept a danger before it <br>overwhelms your ally. Y ou may spend 1 Soma to get between an <br>ally and a danger by standing in their place. Receive 1 Additional <br>Success to any Defense Check you have to perform doing so. Once <br>per Scenario, you can ignore 1 Wound you suffer.<br>I am stronger and faster than any human and I am a highly <br>skilled fighter. I don’t shy away from a challenge because I <br>always believe I can win.<br>• Monkey King: Y ou are able to perform athletic feats <br>unthinkable to a mere mortal. Y ou may spend 1 Soma and choose <br>an effect:<br>1. Y ou can jump incredibly far, up to thirty feet. Y ou can bring <br>another person with you by carrying them on your shoulders. Y ou <br>also ignore any damage related to a fall. <br>2. Use your tail to manipulate an object and perform an additional <br>action.<br>3. Ignore any physical impediments to movement by using your <br>impressive skills.<br>I have no memory of my life before my captivity, although I often dream of the forests <br>and snow-capped peaks of my beloved China. I grew up as a circus animal at London’s <br>Royal Circus but, deep within I carry the conviction that I am destined for something else. I <br>rebelled by killing all my captors, fleeing across a vast and labyrinthine city. When the Order <br>reached me, I thought it was the end, but the Hunters took me with them as their guardian and <br>defender. The more I live as a Hunter, the closer I draw to transcendence. Now I am aware <br>that, someday, I will discover who I really am.<br>My essence is magical, and this makes me resistant to enchantments that <br>might snare stupid humans. My spiritual presence is imposing, and I struggle <br>to hide what I am, especially in the eyes of those accustomed to magic.<br>• Dark Ego - Descendant of the Awakening of the Void and <br>the Emptiness: When you release your true power, your body emits <br>a divine light and no one can stop you. Take 1 Wound to get 2 Additional <br>Successes to any physical Checks you have to perform. For the rest of the <br>Scene spells have little effect on you and you get 2 Additional Successes to any <br>Defense Check you make to protect yourself from arcane effects. When you <br>deal a hit to someone, you can spend 1 Soma to inflict 1 additional Wound. <br>The effects of this Gift cease if you behave in a composed and obedient <br>manner, as your role as guardian dictates.<br>Activator: Act with passion and strength, showing everyone the incredible <br>power that lies within your body.<br>Equipment <br>A circus stick with three segments that I can extend / Old <br>and worn circus clothes / An old golden diadem so tight <br>on my forehead that it cannot be removed / A sheet with <br>the drawing of a Chinese landscape, gift from a child who <br>watched one of my shows.<br>XP<br>Soma<br> 6<br>Wounds <br>1.<br>2.<br>3.<br>Extra <br>Wound.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":2600000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241732,"modifiedTime":1783973241732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"RjpLVgVnFdCYEFUu","name":"Pagina 27","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 27</h2><p>Verdoux Bluebeard</p>","markdown":""},"sort":2700000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241732,"modifiedTime":1783973241732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"k2Q2nxZMEGhGVKwH","name":"Pagina 28","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 28</h2><p>I am a French aristocrat, called upon by my sovereign to manage the most devious and disreputable <br>matters. I have lived an unconventional life, between accomplishing impossible tasks and keeping <br>unspeakable secrets. It has opened my eyes to the world beyond the prosaic limits to which most are <br>accustomed. In an effort to escape my adventurous life, I have more than once tried to start a family. <br>However, my efforts have always ended in ruin, a price I must pay for the secrets I keep. I have lost six <br>lovers, each killed by enemies and dangers that I naively hoped I could exclude from my life. That is why I <br>volunteered for the Order, took an oath to weed out the darkness in this world, and sought revenge for the <br>lives that were stolen from me.<br>Under the facade of a respectable man hides a skilled, unscrupulous <br>problem-solver. I know how to kill and how to act with decisiveness. <br>Everyone has done something they are not proud of and I can’t stand <br>seeing the hypocrites who pretend as if they are morally superior to <br>others.<br>• Dark Ego - The Unscrupulous Assassin:  Y ou may appear as a civilized gentleman, but appearances can be deceiving. When <br>necessary, you will not hesitate to kill. If you eliminate an NPC by inflicting <br>a final Wound, you can also immediately eliminate a second Minor NPC. <br>When you successfully defend yourself from a violent action, you can <br>immediately eliminate a Minor NPC in response. Either way, the target <br>must be within range of your wrath. After inflicting 1 Wound to someone, <br>you can move freely as an additional action, allowing you to reach your <br>true goal without anyone preventing you from doing so.<br>Activator: Reveal your dark side by injuring someone or acting aggressively <br>despite your outwardly calm and staid appearance.<br>XP<br>Soma<br> 6<br>Equipment <br>Nobleman’s clothes / A long black cape / A large <br>bunch of keys / A fine dueling blade / Snuff of <br>excellent quality / A few doses of deadly Aqua <br>Tofana / A large amount of coins and precious <br>trinkets / A heart-shaped locket hanging from a gold <br>chain, within which are engraved the names of my <br>lost loves.<br>Wounds <br>1.<br>2.<br>3.<br>Extra <br>Wound.<br>Verdoux<br>Bluebeard<br>Descriptors and Gifts<br>My specialty is problem solving and I have a talent for analyzing <br>every situation, allowing me to find resources and discover <br>clues. Managing danger requires calm and concentration, <br>and so I hate acting precipitously.<br>• Problem Solver: If you’ve seen it once, you can do it <br>yourself even better. Y ou may spend 1 Soma to replicate the effect <br>of a Gift from a Hunter or NPC you witnessed during the Scenario. <br>Particular Gifts may still be off limits or only yield a part of their <br>effect at the Storyteller’s discretion. Y ou cannot replicate more than <br>one Gift at a time. Once per Scene, you may ask the Storyteller to <br>reveal to you a Gift of an NPC that you had time to study.<br>I am an educated man who has studied the arts and sciences. <br>I use this knowledge to uncover truths and reveal mysteries. I <br>hate secrets, but only when I don’t know them.<br>• The Key to Each Door: Once per Scene, you can use one <br>of the magic keys you own. Choose an effect. <br>1. Open a closed door, no matter how many locks or defenses it <br>has.<br>2. If a subject touches your key, discover the strongest feeling they <br>are experiencing. <br>3. Close and lock a door so that no conventional methods will be <br>able to open it. <br>4. If you put your key in the mouth of a dead person you will see <br>some of their memories. The Storyteller will describe them to you, <br>focusing on your areas of interest.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":2800000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241732,"modifiedTime":1783973241732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"2wu6HL3gYqYh2rkR","name":"Pagina 29","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 29</h2><p>Yukie Onn<br>the Traveling<br>Artist</p>","markdown":""},"sort":2900000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241732,"modifiedTime":1783973241732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"FFaSkLg2tjfFAAFw","name":"Pagina 30","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 30</h2><p>I am a traveling artist who has known fame and honor in my homeland, Japan. That prestige meant nothing, <br>however, when I found true love with Akihiro, son of a powerful noble family. When they forbade him from seeing <br>me, we fled together to the remote region of Ezo. Even there we were not beyond the reach of Akihiro’s family and <br>they pursued us into the high, snow-capped mountains. We had escaped every assassin, but could not outwit the <br>snowstorm that trapped us. I survived, but only because Akihiro sacrificed the warmth of his life to save mine.  <br>But the cold has left me changed. It has become part of me and now the only thing that can make me feel warm <br>is the hot blood of others. After taking revenge on all those who took Akihiro from me, I fled far away, using my <br>talent for art to gain prestige and the protection of wealthy western nobles. Now, in the service of the Order, I <br>save others from suffering the injustice that I have experienced, by punishing selfishness and wickedness.<br>My body is pure ice and, because of this, I can manipulate ice as I please. <br>However, I hate to manifest my power because it is dangerous to those <br>around me and, as an artist, my purpose is to make people smile.<br>• Dark Ego - Ice-Cold: Y ou have control over your body temperature <br>and, consequently, you can freeze the environment or objects in your <br>immediate vicinity. When you manipulate ice, choose an effect by creating <br>a Descriptor that represents it such as: Frozen Door or Aura of Frost and <br>spend 1 Soma to manifest it for the whole Scene. As an additional effect, <br>your frost can inflict 1 Wound on those who interact with it or make what <br>you freeze incredibly fragile or incredibly hard. Whoever exploits the effects <br>of frost in their favor gains 1 Additional Success for their action. Y our frost <br>has no direct effect on living things.<br>Activator: Shed your disguise as a simple artist and reveal your true, bitterly <br>cold form or react passionately when fear and intimidation are used for selfish <br>reasons.<br>XP<br>Soma<br> 6<br>Equipment <br>A travel kimono / Stage kimono, make-up, and stage effects / A <br>small ice sphere that never melts / A butterfly-shaped hair clip, <br>a reminder of my lost love Akihiro / A finely crafted Shamisen, <br>a traditional stringed instrument / Several daggers hidden in the <br>Kimono / A pair of fine fans.<br>Wounds <br>1.<br>2.<br>3.<br>Extra <br>Wound.<br>Yukie Onn<br>the Traveling<br>Artist<br>Descriptors and Gifts<br>I am a highly skilled artist. Music, dance, and painting hold no <br>mysteries for me. My otherworldly charm captivates ordinary <br>people, always drawing attention to me.<br>• Otherworldly Charm:  When you perform or flaunt <br>your talents, all eyes will be on you. Receive 1 Additional Success <br>for each Position Check you make to attract attention or charm <br>someone. If you get an Outcome with an Increment, you may <br>declare that a subject who has seen you has fallen in love with you. <br>The Storyteller will create a specific Agenda for them that leads <br>them to seek your attention.<br>I cannot feel pain and my frail appearance hides surprising <br>physical abilities. Blood is the only thing that can warm me <br>and its smell alone makes me shiver.<br>• Blood-Hot: Once per Scene, you can consume a person’s <br>blood when inflicting 1 non-fatal Wound. Y ou recover 1 Wound, <br>1 Soma and receive some information about your victim such as a <br>memory, an emotion or their heart’s desire. When you drink blood <br>roll a die: if you roll a 1, you lose control and you will kill your <br>victim by draining their blood, unless someone stops you.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":3000000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241732,"modifiedTime":1783973241732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"librarySlug":"bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen-2022-06-29","category":"Core Book","sourceFile":"bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","sourcePath":"Users\\Gamer\\Documents\\Broken Tales KS [ENG]\\bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf"}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241732,"modifiedTime":1783973241732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"N5lfad8HzCyTdWBd","name":"bt-cb-foxcat-sheet-eng-final-screen","pages":[{"_id":"OvudRJ7DMGbz1fsx","name":"PDF local","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h1>bt-cb-foxcat-sheet-eng-final-screen</h1><p><strong>Archivo:</strong> bt-cb-foxcat-sheet-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf</p><p><strong>Paginas:</strong> 2</p><p><a href=\"#source-pdf-omitted\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Abrir PDF dentro de Foundry</a></p>","markdown":""},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241732,"modifiedTime":1783973241732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"vFYuRZPpcvokL010","name":"Pagina 1","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-foxcat-sheet-eng-final-screen - Pagina 1</h2><p>Cunning Machiavelli the Fox <br>and Sly Bischeri<br>the Cat</p>","markdown":""},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241732,"modifiedTime":1783973241732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"0yNCk8uXv4ZVMtik","name":"Pagina 2","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-foxcat-sheet-eng-final-screen - Pagina 2</h2><p>We are two boys who survived and thrived on the street through trickery and deceit. <br>Unfortunately, we made a terrible mistake by choosing a weird old lady as a mark. She <br>turned out to be a goddamn witch. The witch cursed us… And from that day on, every twelve <br>hours, one becomes a Fox and the other a Cat. Bound by this spell, we found a way to make <br>a lot of money, deceiving stupid nobles and rich merchants. The Order has noticed us and <br>taken us under its wing, with the promise of breaking the curse that afflicts us.<br>Cunning Machiavelli <br>the Fox and Sly <br>Bischeri the Cat<br>Cunning’s exclusive Descriptor and Gift<br>I have a natural talent for telling lies, which the Order often uses to its <br>advantage. In spite of my origins, I know a great deal about many things <br>because lying requires planning and preparation. I’m so used to spinning <br>nonsense that I often lie even when I shouldn’t.<br>• Believe in Miracles:  Statements are true until proven otherwise. <br>Once per Scene, you can tell everyone something that will be accepted <br>without question, until the lie is uncovered. The deception will be obvious to <br>your victims at the end of the Scene or once exposed. Receive 1 Additional <br>Success on any Check in which you exploit the lie you have created.<br>Sly’s exclusive Descriptor and Gift<br>A life on the road has taught me to be a skilled thief, which is why <br>the Order uses me to do its dirty work. If I can make a profit out of a <br>situation, I’ll try to. “Everyone for themselves” is my motto.<br>• Rogue: Y ou always make sure you go unnoticed. By pretending to <br>be weak during a Scene, NPCs will overlook you as a target unless you have <br>previously acted against them. By spending 1 Soma, you can flee a Scene or a <br>situation wherever there is a crowd. No one will be able to stop you.<br>Soma<br> 6<br>Note: During the night, use Cunning’s Descriptor, Gift, and equipment, while Sly will be a cat. During the day, use <br>Sly’s Descriptor, Gift, and equipment, while Cunning will be a fox.<br>Common Descriptors and Gifts<br>I will stop at nothing to get what I want, and it only takes me a few seconds <br>to evaluate what is happening and find the right way to take advantage of it. I <br>hate acting alone because there’s no one to take the blame.<br>• Partner in Crime: Y ou are always ready to seize the right opportunity. <br>Once per Scene, if one of your allies acts with your support, they receive 1 <br>Additional Success to their Check. Additionally, once per Scene, if one of your <br>allies achieves an Outcome with an Increment after they have completed their <br>action, you may immediately take an additional action.<br>Like it or not, we are bound by magic. We can share thoughts, each see <br>what the other sees, and thanks to this we can work together to cheat others. <br>Whoever is in animal form hates not being able to communicate and often <br>annoys the other out of spite.<br>• Dark Ego - The Fox and the Cat:  The curse that binds you makes <br>you a perfect team. At night as Cunning or during the day as Sly, you are a human <br>and make use of the full support of your partner in his animal form. Y our <br>partner can act individually to accomplish the task you give him. Y ou share the <br>same Wounds and the same Soma. Whoever is in human form can spend 1 Soma <br>to use the Gift of his accomplice. Once per Scene, if your partner is there to help <br>you, you receive 2 Additional Successes on a Position Check.<br>Activator: Trick or deceive someone, taking advantage of the support of your <br>trusted partner in crime.<br>XP<br>Cunning’s Equipment<br>Comfortable and light clothes / A set of small knives that I hide everywhere <br>/ Cards, stamps, and other counterfeit objects / Some completely fake coins and jewelry / A volume of the famous Biblioteca Universale Sacro-<br>Profana Encyclopedia, which always reveals what I need to know.<br>Sly’s Equipment<br>Worn-out and lived-in clothes / A long, sharp knife / An old stick to <br>pretend to be blind / An old purse with a hole in it / A sack full of junk <br>that I collect while thieving.<br>Wounds <br>1.<br>2.<br>3.<br>Extra <br>Wound.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241732,"modifiedTime":1783973241732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"librarySlug":"bt-cb-foxcat-sheet-eng-final-screen-2022-06-29","category":"Core Book","sourceFile":"bt-cb-foxcat-sheet-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","sourcePath":"Users\\Gamer\\Documents\\Broken Tales KS [ENG]\\bt-cb-foxcat-sheet-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf"}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241733,"modifiedTime":1783973241733,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"4yOY40LTdtSlr6F8","name":"Broken Europe Map","pages":[{"_id":"Bcghkm3OiA7SG8lB","name":"PDF local","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h1>Broken Europe Map</h1><p><strong>Archivo:</strong> Broken Europe Map.pdf</p><p><strong>Paginas:</strong> 1</p><p><a href=\"#source-pdf-omitted\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Abrir PDF dentro de Foundry</a></p>","markdown":""},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241733,"modifiedTime":1783973241733,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"sOyP6GKISvnvjkJ8","name":"Pagina 1","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>Broken Europe Map - Pagina 1</h2><p>Map<br>Broken Europe<br>City<br>Settlement<br>Bridge<br>Forest<br>Naples<br>Rome<br>Paris Prague<br>London<br>York<br>Martana Island<br>Sinalunga<br>Borgo <br>Maleanime<br>Valea Viilor<br>Durfort<br>Whitehaven<br>Vík í Mýrdal<br>Borgholm<br>Stegeborg<br>Malbork<br>Lohr<br>Nijmegen<br>ZugarramurdiVigo<br>Devil's <br>Bridge<br>Black <br>Forest<br>Devil's <br>Bridge<br>Devil's <br>Bridge<br>BEAUTIFUL A SUNNY <br>DAY! THE SPELL IS BROKEN A SMALL ROAD IN THE WOODS DARK BEARD MEMORIES WHY?<br> FAIRYTALE A GENTLE CARESS A SMALL TOY SOMETHING OF VALUE</p>","markdown":""},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241733,"modifiedTime":1783973241733,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"librarySlug":"broken-europe-map","category":"Sheets and Support","sourceFile":"Broken Europe Map.pdf","sourcePath":"Users\\Gamer\\Documents\\Broken Tales KS [ENG]\\Broken Europe Map.pdf"}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241733,"modifiedTime":1783973241733,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"7ulIzrjrUfWkuQqo","name":"Broken Tales - Bookmarks","pages":[{"_id":"pTHUFxwRBJeMmurB","name":"PDF local","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h1>Broken Tales - Bookmarks</h1><p><strong>Archivo:</strong> Broken Tales - Bookmarks [2022-06-30].pdf</p><p><strong>Paginas:</strong> 1</p><p><a href=\"#source-pdf-omitted\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Abrir PDF dentro de Foundry</a></p>","markdown":""},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241746,"modifiedTime":1783973241746,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"c8NZitnlFgb6Pmv1","name":"Pagina 1","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>Broken Tales - Bookmarks - Pagina 1</h2><p>Bookmark<br>Additional Descriptors<br>Story Gifts<br>Wounds<br>Notes<br>Soma    XP<br>Once upon a time...<br>Sheet<br> ←<br> ←<br>Additional Descriptors<br>Story Gifts<br>Wounds<br>Notes<br>Soma    XP<br>Once upon a time...<br>Sheet<br> ←<br> ←</p>","markdown":""},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241746,"modifiedTime":1783973241746,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"librarySlug":"broken-tales-bookmarks-2022-06-30","category":"Sheets and Support","sourceFile":"Broken Tales - Bookmarks [2022-06-30].pdf","sourcePath":"Users\\Gamer\\Documents\\Broken Tales KS [ENG]\\Broken Tales Sheets ENG\\Broken Tales - Bookmarks [2022-06-30].pdf"}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241746,"modifiedTime":1783973241746,"lastModifiedBy":null